data.text:
NEWARK, N.J. — The Lakers are scheduled to practice Monday in Washington before they have their community-service event and meeting with President Obama in the afternoon, so Andrew Bynum should be on track to make his season debut Tuesday vs. the Wizards.

Bynum said Monday that he wanted a couple more practices so he wouldn’t feel “too foreign” in his first game after July 28 surgery to reattach cartilage in his right knee. He got some 3-on-3 action with Lakers reserves Thursday before the team left for Chicago, and now he’ll get this workout in Washington.

Phil Jackson said he wants to see how things go for Bynum his his one more practice before any determinations are made.
